@startuml

actor "Internal Admin" as Admin
participant "User Management Portal" as UMP
participant "Microsoft Entra ID" as Entra
participant "Application API" as API
database "Application SQL DB" as DB
participant "Email Service" as Email
actor "External User" as User
participant "Client Portal" as Portal
participant "Azure AD B2C" as B2C


== INTERNAL USER LOGIN ==

Admin -> UMP : Access User Management Portal
UMP -> Entra : Redirect for SSO Authentication
Entra -> Admin : Login + MFA
Entra -> UMP : ID Token + Access Token
UMP -> UMP : Validate token & roles

UMP -> Admin : Admin Dashboard


== CREATE EXTERNAL USER INVITATION ==

Admin -> UMP : Create External User\n(Name, Email, Role)

UMP -> API : POST /external-users
API -> DB : Save user record\nStatus = INVITED

API -> API : Generate InvitationToken

API -> DB : Update record\nInvitationToken

API -> Email : Send Invitation Email\nRegistration Link

Email -> User : Email with link\n/register?token=ABC123


== USER OPENS INVITATION LINK ==

User -> Portal : Open registration link

Portal -> API : Validate invitation token

API -> DB : Find invitation by token

DB -> API : Return user record

API -> Portal : Token valid\nReturn invited email


== REDIRECT TO ADB2C SIGNUP ==

Portal -> Portal : Generate OAuth state\nstate = InvitationToken

Portal -> B2C : Redirect to Signup\nstate=ABC123


== USER REGISTRATION IN ADB2C ==

User -> B2C : Enter email & password

B2C -> B2C : Create Identity

B2C -> Portal : Return ID Token\nstate=ABC123


== VALIDATE REGISTRATION ==

Portal -> Portal : Extract state (token)

Portal -> API : POST /complete-registration\n(Token + ID Token)

API -> API : Decode ID Token

API -> DB : Lookup invitation token

DB -> API : Return invited email


alt Email matches invited email

API -> DB : Update user record\nStatus = ACTIVE\nSave B2C ObjectId

API -> Portal : Registration successful

Portal -> User : Redirect to Client Dashboard


else Email mismatch

API -> Portal : Registration rejected

Portal -> User : Error\n"Email does not match invitation"

end


== LOGIN FLOW AFTER REGISTRATION ==

User -> Portal : Access Client Portal

Portal -> B2C : Redirect to Login

User -> B2C : Enter credentials

B2C -> Portal : Return ID Token

Portal -> API : Validate user

API -> DB : Lookup by B2C ObjectId

DB -> API : Return user profile

API -> Portal : User authorized

Portal -> User : Dashboard Access


@enduml